Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteSpareModule(25.10)                              deleteSpareModule(25.10)

Name
       deleteSpareModule - Deletes the instantiation of a created spare module
       and all the spare instances under the hinst

Syntax
        deleteSpareModule hInst<Name>

       Deletes  the  instantiation of a created spare module and all the spare
       instances under the hinst.

Parameters
       <hInstName>
              Specifies the instantiation to delete.

Example
       The following code shows the creation of the spare module SPGM,  place-
       ment of the module and its instances in the design, and deletion of the
       hInst of "SPGM_spr_1":

       #create a spare module

       createSpareModule  -moduleName  SPGM  -cell  {DFFNSRX2  INVX4 \ NOR2X2}
       -clock sysclk

       #instantiation the spare module and place them in the design

       placeSpareModule -moduleName SPGM -channel -minWidth 4.7 -maxWidth 10 \
       -minLength 11 -stepx 10 -stepy 10 -util 0.6

       #delete one instantiation of the spare module

        deleteSpareModule top/SPGM_spr_1

